      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Well, the CIF insurance, when properly arranged, is generally designed to cover the main perils of the sea, which includes things like severe weather, sinking, and even piracy. These are usually covered under the Institute Cargo Clauses, which are the standard terms. However, you must ensure the policy includes \"all risks\" or at least covers specific perils like \"perils of the sea\" and \"theft.\" If the loss is due to something truly unpredictable or excluded by the policy, then yes, you might be on the hook, which is why you should always scrutinize the policy wording.",
      "source": "target",
